-- Finnish Golfer Mikko Ilonen Wins Nordea Masters by Three Shots
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-06-02T16:27:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-02/finnish-golfer-mikko-ilonen-wins-nordea-masters-by-three-shots.html
Mikko Ilonen of Finland had a final-round 69, 3-under par, to win golf’s Nordea Masters by three
shots for his first European Tour victory in six years.  Ilonen finished on 21 under par in Stockholm, with Jonas
Blixt of Sweden second and Austria’s Bernd Wiesberger third, a
shot further back. Ilonen’s previous win was at the Scandinavian
Masters in 2007.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 